```class Solution {
    public int minInsertions(String s) {
        int res = 0, left = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '(') left++;
            else if (left == 0) res++;
            else left--;
        }
        return res + left;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: We iterate through the string once, keeping track of the number of open parentheses and the number of insertions needed. When we encounter a closing parenthesis and there are no open parentheses to match it, we increment the insertion count. At the end, we add the remaining open parentheses to the insertion count.

